cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation for wireless video transmission, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video streaming and transmission, which falls under the multimedia category. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel solution for resource allocation based on weight distribution, which can be related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for real-time video streaming in wireless personal area networks, which can be related to systems and control. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper mentions the use of H.264/AVC encoding for surveillance videos, which can be related to computer vision and pattern recognition.
